A man has been rescued after falling 30ft down a cliff onto a river bank.The Scottish Fire and Rescue Service (SFRS) were called to Field Road in Busby, East Renfrewshire just before 3pm to help the 34-year-old.Firefighters used specialist rope rescue equipment to rescue the man who had fallen onto the banks of the White Cart Water.He was brought back to the top of the cliff just after 4pm and passed to the care of the Scottish Ambulance Service.The man was then taken to the South Glasgow University Hospital.